### Strategic Insight Note:
**Data Gap/Observation:** While granular HNI income data is private, the ₹6 Cr price point in Mumbai currently correlates with a **"High-Earning Professional / Second-Generation Entrepreneur"** demographic. The market signal indicates a shift away from "investment-first" (buying to rent out) toward "consumption-first" (buying for personal status and utility). Buyers at this level are increasingly wary of "ghost apartments"—high-priced units that lack a vibrant, high-net-worth community—which is why the *reputation of the developer* currently outweighs *square footage* in their decision matrix.